Last week I did a story about an Amityville non-profit called “Keep Your Change” - an academic program to empower students to achieve their fullest potential. 
•
Every year they have a Christmas dinner & give donations to 7 homeless shelters in Suffolk county. The donations they collect are called “Blessings in a Box”. The idea behind it is to fill up a box with essential items (soap, toothbrush, etc) that would help someone who is displaced. 
•
With so many people struggling financially his year Executive Director, Dr Pam Robinson-Allen told me they weren’t going to have enough Blessings in a Box to give out to the more than 300 displaced people showing up to their event on Saturday.
•
My story aired on News 12 on Monday, and I prayed that the story would reach out and motivate people to donate. But I walked away from Dr Pam that day feeling like I needed to do more. As reporters and videographers we see a lot out in the field and really feel the emotions of our stories. This story was one of them. I came home still thinking about those blessings in a box. I was talking to friends about it, and they gave me that extra boost to start texting/calling/reaching out to other friends and before I knew it my living room was full of these boxes my friends put together & donated! 
•
Late Friday night we dropped off those boxes to Dr Pam and I was so happy to see those boxes were part of at least 300 other boxes in the room. Mission accomplished! 
•
Those blessings in a box may just be essential items but it means a lot to the recipients. It gives them dignity, it lets them know others care about them. That they are loved. Isn’t that what Christmas is all about? ❤️
•

Brentwood Varsity High School qualified for Nationals in Florida…And the team is super excited! 
•
They needed a minimum of $5,000 to pay for costs involved for their trip to Florida to compete. 
•
I’m happy to report that after our story aired last night, the team reached their goal through a go fund me page set up by the cheerleading coach!! 
•
And today, theres an update and even more positive news! The community of Brentwood and beyond are reaching out to the students with more help. So stay tuned!!
•
This fundraising goal was extra tough because two of the cheer girls in particular were struggling financially. They were victims of two separate house fires in the month of January, where they lost their homes and all of their belongings including their cheer equipment! 
•
After talking with the girls on the team, I could see their camaraderie, the sisterhood and strength they share. Even though they’re hurting inside, they put on their smiles and showed their enthusiasm, knowing they’re a part of something bigger than cheer.
•
Nationals take place on February 10th and we wish these bright students lots of luck! 
Go Big Green!

🇮🇹 Preserving The Past 🇮🇹 
•
This was such a beautiful project to be a part of that involved my own heritage. “Preserving The Past” was a half hour special about different cultures in the tri-state area. We got to tell the stories of two inspiring and passionate Italian-Americans who are passing their knowledge and skills down to the next generation here on Long Island.
•
Thank goodness I had the creative team of Videographer Pat Mantle @patrizioxc76 and producer Chris Vaccaro @chrisvaccaro who were absolutely wonderful! 
•
Thank you to Master Italian Tailor Sebastiano Montella and his daughter Michelina who were extremely gracious and took the time to show me the importance of quality fabrics & craftsmanship

*Warning* this may be graphic
•
I was able to get this exclusive video of a shooting that happened Saturday night at 9:45 PM on Spencer Place in Hempstead. 
•
In the first video - you can see in the right hand corner, a suspect shooting toward a group of people on the sidewalk. The family who lives in the home tell me that they were celebrating their 4-year-old nephew’s birthday last night when someone fired 10 shots toward the group and hit 4 people. All 4 were taken to the hospital and are expected to be OK.
•
In the second video - in the top right hand corner, you can see the scene from across the street of the suspect running away. 
•
I’ll have the full story tonight at 5 PM on  @news12li

Congressman George Santos was taken into federal custody this morning. 

••••UPDATE•••• 

Santos has pleaded not guilty, he is being released on a $500,000 bond.

Seven counts of wire fraud, three counts of money laundering, one count of theft of public funds, and two counts of making materially false statements to the House of Representatives.

🥒 My morning breakfast shake routine 🥒 
•
Thought I would share my green shake recipe I have every morning. It gets me ready for the day, puts my mind/gut in a good place and it cuts down on cravings 
•
Banana, cucumber, pineapple, ginger, water, @1stphorm Greens powder, @bubsnaturals MCT Oil Powder, & pure maca magic powder.
•
Sometimes I add protein powder, depending on the day. I’m allergic to Whey Protein so I use Egg White protein. 
•
Everyone has a different recipe, if you don’t like something just replace it w/a similar equivalent. 
Blend it up and enjoy! 
•

•
